ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You have to take it. The seminars probably aren't at a time you can go as a first year.
Attending the inorganic seminars is a great opportunity for the students to learn more about different areas the field. I would definitely recommend that students attend as many as they possibly can.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I found most of the seminars to be very enjoyable and engaging. As the topic differed seminar to seminar, some of the seminars were more relevant to my work/research than others were. They do undoubtedly contribute to the Yale Chemistry Department as a whole.
Learned a lot from outside speakers.
